dy": "I would like to get feedback on the purpose of `download-url` now that we have `addurls`. There is a significant overlap. Additionally `download-url` needs an overhaul wrt path handling (e.g. use of `normpath` inside), i.e. transition it to use pathlib.\r\n\r\nQ is now: is there anything that speaks against stripping any functionality from `download-url` that works with datasets (e.g. actually saving downloaded files in a dataset)?\r\n\r\n#### Pros\r\n\r\n- it would make the command do what the name suggests -- download and download only\r\n- it would reduce the overlap with `addurls`\r\n\r\n#### Cons\r\n\r\n- it complicates adding a single/few files to a dataset from a set of URLs (but given there is `git annex addurl`, and `addurls` not much is lost)", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3643/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3643/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}